HOUSES HOUSE

Rules and Procedures for Townhouses on Age of Legends

To request a townhouse, simply email majere@ageoflegends.com. Include your character name and the location of the house you'd like to purchase. Also, if you see Majere on, you can send him a tell asking for one. 

To request a Guild Hall, e-mail majere@ageoflegends.com. 

To request a custom house, email majere@ageoflegends.com. Include the following information with your request. Incomplete requests cannot be processed. 

1. The name of the character purchasing the house as well as the name of any guest that you wish to allow to full access to the house (currently, you may have up to one guest). 

2. The housing option you wish to purchase (Option I, II, or III). 

3. Room descriptions for each room that you are purchasing. The descriptions are subject to approval, but, we are rather liberal with what is allowed. 

4. Object descriptions for each object you wish to purchase (remember that you will see information when you look at an object, so be sure to include how you would like this to read). The descriptions are subject to approval, but we are rather liberal with what is allowed. 

5. A preferred location for your house. This, like the descriptions, are subject to final approval. We try to reasonably accommodate all requests, but you may be denied your first choice. Custom housing cannot be put into a city and needs to fit into the area specified. If you aren't sure exactly where you would like it, just indicate that you would like a few options and include a little information about your character so that we might make a helpful suggestion or two. Please note that your house must be at least 20 rooms away from a city with townhouses in it. At this time that includes: Kalaman, Karthay, Lacynes, and Morning Dew. 

You will be mailed if there is a problem with any of the descriptions or your preferred location. Again, we do try to make every effort to meet your requests while working to maintain consistency in our world.

Below are the options and pricing available for housing on Age of Legends. 

Townhouse (subject to availability) 

Purchase Cost = 20p 
Monthly Taxes = 14p

------------------------------------ 

Option I - Two rooms 
Includes a maximum of 2 objects. 

Purchase Cost = 50p 
Monthly Taxes = 44p 

------------------------------------ 

Option II - Three rooms 
Includes a maximum of 3 objects. 

Purchase Cost = 55p 
Monthly Taxes = 52p 

------------------------------------ 

Option III - Four rooms 
Includes a maximum of 4 objects. 

Purchase Cost = 60p 
Monthly Taxes = 60p 

------------------------------------ 

Each custom house has to consist of at least two rooms. If a player only wants one room, then you may get a townhouse, if one is available. 

A maximum of four rooms is allowed for custom housing. This includes if you have a guest in your house. 

You may include, with your request, one item for each room, one of which may be a wear item. This includes things like furniture, paintings, rugs, tapestries, fireplaces, food, drink, etc. Any food items will be placed in a pantry in the kitchen for retrieval. If you would like a lockable door/entryway, the key count as one of the objects for your house. All worn items will have no stats and be level one, they are purely for show. 

Monthy rent is calculated by what option you select. The building cost is only needed when the house is first bought, after that, you only have to pay the monthly taxes. 

A few things to note: 
-No items made for a house will be sellable. 
-Locks on houses will be pickable. 
-You can allow chars into your house to visit, but they will not have access to the area where items can be dropped or where you can rent. 
-New houses will be added to the world as soon as we can. To gain access to the house you must get it paid for. 
-Townhouses can be purchased at any time, however the cost and a full month's taxes are still payable upon purchase (we do not prorate the monthly taxes). 

Rules (Please read since violation of the rules can result in loss of the house): 
-Owners of the house are responsible for all associated costs and payments. 
-Rent/Taxes are due at the beginning of the month (using the RL calendar). It is the primary owners responsibility to make sure that their taxes are paid in time. They must make every effort to get the fees to the designated imm in charge of housing. 
-Players may drop/store one object for each wear location within their house. Drop items ONLY in the room where you have been told they will be saved. This will be the room that only you and/or your guest have access to. Any additional items (extra clothing, food, potions, etc) must be rented. There will be a housekeeper available so that you may rent within your house. 
-Any excess items dropped (more than one item for each wear location slot) will be purged, starting with the most expensive/powerful/rare item. Repeat offenders may have the whole room purged or lose their house. Dropping any key other than your own house key will result in the entire contents of the room being purged. 

