RANGER

Rangers are the men and women of the wilderness, striving for the defense and
flourishing of nature.  They are superb woodsmen and excel at such skills of 
the wild.  Also able warriors, rangers will use most weapons, save the most 
cumbersome and intricate, preferring the subtlety of nature.  They will wear 
no armor heavier than chain mail, and even then usually prefer the lightest 
mesh possible.  Rangers are, like paladins, holy warriors although of a 
different sort.  The most adept of there kind receive some spells from their 
patron God.  Rangers must have above average physical skills and must possess
more wisdom and worldliness than the normal person.

See also: PRACTICE
#
ROGUE THIEF ASSASSIN

Rogues are masters of deception. They excel at moving about silently and 
concealing themselves in a variety of ways from others. They are also expert
hunters, with a number of abilities that allow them to follow their prey 
virtually anywhere. Although some rogues are light-hearted fellows who use 
their deceptive abilities for pranks, many walk the darker paths of life 
and use their skills only to bring about personal gain and the downfall of 
others. This class is a combination of the former thief and assassin classes.

See also: PRACTICE
